Project Chattisgarh

Accelerate growth of Chhattisgarh’s farming community, its rural economy and further green the state. Chhattisgarh is one of the richest bio-diverse states of the country and is known as the rice bowl of central India for cultivating paddy as its principal crop. It’s favorable soil, climatic conditions and vast amount of arable land available for cultivation has made it a leading producer of a variety of coarse grains. With the potential to become a dominant producer of fruit orchards, SankalpTaru Foundation with the help from our donors will help Chhattisgarh agriculture gain a new momentum towards an economically viable phase.
